Sweet Potato Platter 🙌🏻 Is it acceptable to just eat this for dinner? 😜 I mean, it has 3 different dips so that basically covers all the food bases.... right? Made this to enjoy while we watch some football tonight because I always have to have snacks in front of me 🤷🏼‍♀️ Snacks that are centered around dips are my personal favorite, but I don’t get too picky haha. I cut the sweet potatoes into different shapes just for fun because it keeps things interesting and it’s no extra work. Perfect little appetizer for Sundays watching football 🏈 or bachelor Monday’s which sadly aren’t a thing rn 🙄 which dip would be your fav?! I’m an avocado gal thru and thru 🙌🏻 -
-
recipe details 👉🏻 4 small sweet potatoes sliced into chips and fries and coated with 2 tbsp of avocado oil (can use any oil) and sprinkled with pink Himalayan salt and pepper. Kept the flavor simple so I could have more flavor in the dips. Baked at 425F for 35 mins. Paired with @traderjoes everything but the bagel dip (soooo good) + mashed avocado + @aldiusa salsa

Crunchwrap Supreme 🤤 
Ingredients
- Iceburg Lettuce - Tomato
- Cheese
- Beef
- Tacobell fire sauce
- Sour cream
- Tostada shell
- Large flour tortilla
- Mexican or taco seasoning

Instructions

Taco seasoning mix: 1 TBS Cumin, 1 TBS Chilli powder, ½ TBS Paprika, 1 TBS Garlic powder, 1 TBS Onion powder, ½ TBS Cayenne, ½ TBS oregano, 1 TBS Salt, ½ TBS Black pepper, ¼ TBS chili flakes, mix all together

Ground beef: season beef with 1 TBS Mexican seasoning and mix, and add to a pan on high heat with large drizzle of olive oil, break it up in the pan with a wooden spoon and keep it on the heat til the water starts to evaporate and the beef starts to fry in its own fat, approx 7-10 mins, but you will heat it go from boiling to frying, then add a touch of flour to create a sort of sauce to go with the meat 
Building: take a 12” (preferably) flour tortilla and make a tostada size layer of beef in the middle, add a tostada shell with sour cream on top, add shredded or sliced iceberg lettuce, diced tomatoes, and cheese (any kind) I used cheddar

Folding: take any edge of tortilla and fold in, then at corner either corner fold in, and continue in same direction all the way around

Toasting: on same pan you cooked ground beef toast the crunch wrap on high heat about 2 minutes each side or till you see some color

HOJE EU FIZ LASANHA 🥰😍 tentei gravar nos stories mas não ia os meus vídeos 😢 falava que tinha sido bloqueado. Mas já temos essa belezura no Canal ❤️🙌🏻 o link está na bio 🙋🏼‍♀️.
Vou escrever aqui pra vocês novamente 👇🏻
Só um minuto

MASSA DA PANQUECA
02 ovos
02 colheres de sopa de azeite 
1/2 xícara de leite
01 xícara de farinha de trigo
Sal
Bate no liquidificador e pronto.
Com uma frigideira untada com manteiga faça as panquecas e separe.
O frango você desfia (útilizei 01 peito)
1/2 cebola picada
Frita.. alho a gosto.
Pimenta de cheiro
Tomate a gosto
E acrescenta o frango. Mexe e depois azeitonas, sal a gosto. 01 caixa de creme de leite e 01 pacote de molho de tomate pronto.
Reserva
Molho branco
02 colheres de sopa de manteiga
02 colheres de sopa de farinha de trigo,
Mexe até dissolver e depois 02 xícaras de leite, sal e pimenta de reino.
Mexe até engrossar e levantar fervura. 
AGORA A MONTAGEM
Primeira camada molho branco, panqueca, frango e muçarela.
E depois finaliza da mesma forma. 
Por último o queijo 🧀 .
Forno por 25 min no forno até derreter o queijo.
SINCERAMENTE ? Bem melhor do que macarrão 😛
Ficou uma delicia 😋

⁣ChocoFlan🍮🍫😍🤤⁣
⁣⁣
🔷Ingredientes:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🔹Para el caramelo necesitaremos:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1/2 taza de azucar blanca⁣⁣
1/4 de taza de agua⁣⁣
Ingredientes para el quesillo o flan⁣⁣
5 huevos⁣⁣
1 lata de leche condensada de 395 gr⁣⁣
395 gr de leche (usaremos la medida de la lata de la leche condensada)⁣⁣
1 cucharada de vainilla⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🔹Ingredientes para la torta húmeda de chocolate:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
4 huevos⁣⁣
1 y 1/2 taza de harina de trigo⁣⁣
1 taza de cacao o chocolate en polvo (no instantáneo)⁣⁣
1 y 1/2 taza de azúcar⁣⁣
1/2 taza de leche⁣⁣
1/2 taza de aceite⁣⁣
1 cucharada de polvo de hornear (10 gr)⁣⁣
Molde Corona de 24 cm de diametro o uno redondo de 20 cm.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🔶 Preparación:⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1) Lo primero que vamos hacer es el caramelo y lo vamos a colocar en nuestro molde como si estuviésemos haciendo un flan.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2) Luego comenzamos hacer la mezcla de chocolate, que sería nuestro pastel, cuando esté lista la vertemos en el molde, de ultimo hacemos la mezcla del flan, y lo vertemos en el centro de nuestra preparación, lo llevamos al horno 180 grados centígrados. Por 35 minutos para verificar que esté lista introducimos un palito de madera si sale limpio esta lista.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Este pastel lo vamos a colocar en el horno a baño maria.⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Cordon Bleu de Pollo😍⁣
⁣
¿Se les antoja uno así para comer🤤? Aquí les dejamos la #Receta 👇🏻👨🏻‍🍳⁣
⁣
🔷Ingredientes:⁣
⁣
-3/4 kilogramo milanesas de pollo⁣
-Queso amarillo, 1/4 kilogramos⁣
-Jamón rebanado, 1/4 kilogramos⁣
-1/4 taza de harina de trigo⁣
-1 huevo batido con una cucharadita de agua⁣
-1/2 taza de pan rallado⁣
-1/4 taza de mantequilla⁣
-Sal y pimienta.⁣
⁣
🔶Preparación:⁣
⁣
1) Rebanar las milanesas delgadas, golpearlas con un mazo para que se adelgacen.⁣
⁣
2) Colocar encima de cada milanesa, jamón y queso amarillo.⁣
⁣
3) Enrrollamos y colocamos un palillo para que no se desarme.⁣
⁣
4) La harina la sazonamos con sal y pimienta.⁣
⁣
5) Pasamos la milanesa rellena y enrollada, por la harina, huevo y pan rallado.⁣
⁣
6) Refrigeramos por horas, cuando lo vamos a cocinar se sacan de la nevera una media hora antes.⁣
⁣
7) Calentamos la mantequilla y pasamos las milanesas a la mantequilla.⁣
⁣
8) Cocinamos tapado por unos 7 minutos aproximadamente, volteamos y cuando esté listo. Servir con salsa blanca bechamel.⁣
⁣

Acompanhamento obrigatório da brasileiríssima feijoada, tem tantas qualidades que pode deixar de ser coadjuvante e assumir o papel principal. “É uma das dez hortaliças mais ricas em vitaminas e sais minerais”, afirma a nutricionista Carolina Pimentel, professora da Universidade Paulista.⠀
⠀
Fornece fibras e compostos fenólicos que protegem contra danos provocados pelos radicais livres — com isso, podem ter ação preventiva contra tumores da bexiga, mama, estômago e pele.⠀
⠀
As qualidades se estendem aos talos. Por isso, aproveite tudo. E varie no preparo: um dia sirva refogada ou cozida, no outro na salada ou no suco verde. Quando submetida ao calor, perde vitaminas, mas o teor de carotenoides vai lá pra cima.⠀
⠀
Vale lembrar que o tempo de armazenamento da couve congelada aumenta quando as folhas são submetidas ao branqueamento antes de irem para o freezer. É assim: mergulhe o vegetal já lavado em água fervente, deixe alguns minutos e, em seguida, afunde em água gelada. O choque térmico preserva cor, sabor e nutrientes. | Ilustração: Lauro Fonte⠀
⠀

O milho é o cereal mais cultivado no mundo. Além do tipo amarelo tradicional, há as versões branca, rosa, preta, rajada, mais dura, mais mole, doce, com espigas longas ou pequenas. Apesar dessa diversidade de apresentações, o alimento tem participado pouco do dia a dia do brasileiro. Uma pena.⠀
⠀ “O milho é fonte saudável de energia porque possui carboidrato complexo, absorvido lentamente na corrente sanguínea. Isso evita picos de açúcar e faz o corpo gastar mais calorias para aproveitá-lo”, elogia a médica Marcella Garcez Duarte, da Associação Brasileira de Nutrologia.⠀
⠀
O alimento também reúne proteína. Inclusive, se for combinado com uma leguminosa, como feijão ou lentilha, fornece todos os aminoácidos essenciais de que o corpo precisa para formar músculos, cabelos, unhas, hormônios e anticorpos. Traz um pouco de gordura, mas do tipo benéfico, o suficiente para transportar sua vitamina E, bem-vinda ao coração, por exemplo.⠀
⠀
Ainda vem com fibras, que estimulam o trabalho do intestino, melhoram o controle do colesterol e do açúcar no sangue e dão saciedade.⠀ ⠀
O milho concentra vitaminas do complexo B, como a B1, que é essencial para o bom humor, além de minerais, a exemplo de magnésio, potássio, fósforo e cobre, que participam de várias funções no organismo — incluindo o controle da pressão arterial. Um grande atrativo é a presença de antioxidantes, capazes de deter os radicais livres, moléculas instáveis que agridem as células e favorecem doenças.⠀
⠀
O destaque do grupo são os carotenoides, mais especificamente betacaroteno, luteína e zeaxantina — eles que colorem os grãos de amarelo, laranja e vermelho. “Quanto mais intensa a cor, maior o teor desses ingredientes”, ressalta Marcella. Um combo de respeito. ⠀
⠀
Quer saber mais sobre a biografia do milho? Acesse aqui: https://bit.ly/2oZKRFp⠀
⠀

Não se iluda! Chás industrializados não fazem bem para saúde!
.
🔹O chá pronto além de ter muito açúcar ou adoçante tem aromatizantes artificiais, conservantes e é embalado em alumínio ou plástico, que transfere substâncias prejudiciais ao produto.
.
🔸O chá de saquinho não é tão ruim, mas infelizmente o saquinho feito de fios de nylon transfere também substâncias do plástico à bebida.
.
🔹O chá de verdade é de folhas ou talos, frescos ou secos da planta. Feito na hora e sem plástico aquecido!
.
🔸️Você pode fazer seus chás pela manhã e beber ao longo do dia, mantendo-se refrigerados. Duram cerca de 8 a 12h! 🥰
.

Uma delícia para o café da tarde! Vegano e sem glúten! Que tal? A nossa receita ainda leva uma pitada de canela. Experimente!

Ingredientes
1 xícara (chá) de Farinha de Arroz Urbano
1 xícara (chá) de fécula de batata 
1 xícara (chá) de açúcar demerara 
1 colher (sopa) de fermento em pó 
3 maçãs pequenas picadas
1 colher (sopa) de canela em pó 
½ xícara (chá) de gel de linhaça (ovo de linhaça) 
1 xícara (chá) de óleo
1 pitada de sal 
Modo de preparo
No liquidificador, coloque o gel de linhaça, o óleo e as cascas das maçãs. Aos poucos, adicione os ingredientes secos, já peneirados e vá misturando bem. Adicione as maçãs picadas e coloque em forminhas de silicone ou papel manteiga, untadas. Leve para assar em forno preaquecido, por 180 °C, por cerca de 20 a 30 minutos, desinforme e sirva!

Hoje eu queria falar um pouco sobre a aveia, um alimento incrível e cheio de benefícios mas que recentemente sofreu com algumas notícias falsas ao seu respeito.⠀
⠀
Então, vamos tentar desmistificar um pouco esse assunto.⠀
⠀
A aveia é um alimento de alto valor nutritivo rica vitaminas do complexo B, vitamina E, cálcio, ferro e em um tipo de fibra solúvel conhecida como Beta-glucana, esta ajuda a melhorar seu trânsito intestinal e, consequentemente, a lentificar a absorção dos carboidratos, evitando assim picos exacerbados de insulina.⠀
⠀
Alguns estudos mostram que essas fibras possuem um efeito interessante na redução dos nossos triglicerídeos e do colesterol ruim. Além disso, não podemos esquecer que a aveia é extremamente versátil e vai bem com tudo.⠀
⠀
Gostaram da dica? Compartilha com seu amigo que precisa saber desses benefícios! 😁💩⠀
⠀

🥚 Para os veganos ou alérgicos, aqui vão algumas substituições:
.
🔹Grãomelete: bata 1 xíc. de grão de bico deixados de molho com 1/2 xíc. de água no liquidificador, mixer ou com um garfo, junto com alho, manjericão, ou temperos de sua preferência. Depois desepeje tudo em uma frigideira e faça seu omelete normalmente.
.
🔸Tofu mexido: amasse a quantidade desejada de tofu, acrescente cúrcuma, pimenta do reino, orégano e sal. Coloque em uma frigideira, mexa bem e pronto!
.
🔸Pasta de amendoim ou gel de linhaça: esses são dois substitutos para fazer uma massa de bolo. 1 ovo equivale à 1 colher de sopa de farinha de linhaça + 40ml de água ou 1 col. sopa de pasta de amendoim.
.
🔹Banana e chia: misture 1 banana amassada e 2 colheres de sopa cheias de chia. Espere 10min e leve ao fogo em frigideira antiaderente. .

Which side do YOU relate to?! 🤔🤔
. 
By far the biggest question I get is “When will I stop wanting to eat ALL of the things?!?!” Every time I get asked this I have to stop and smile. 😉Why? Because I’ve TOTALLY been there! But, it doesn’t have to be that way.🙅‍♀️
. 
There is what I call the “social media way” of intuitive eating and the No Food Rules way. With the social media way you open up the flood gates and eat ALL of the previously restricted foods at once. 🍕🍫🍰🧁This leaves you feeling out of control and only wanting to go back to restricting immediately! 🙈With the No Food Rules way we work through your food rules one by one, in a specific way, so that you avoid becoming a ping pong ball in a cruel game of diet culture VS food freedom. 🏓This allows you to feel more comfortable- physically and mentally!- during your food freedom journey!🙌🏻
. 
Take the No Food Rules Quiz to identify what is holding you back from finding food freedom and get a workbook tailored to YOU that will help you implement the No Food Rules framework! 🤩Did I mention the quiz [link in bio] is free ninety nine?😘

🌮😍 Healthy spinach tortillas! 📷 by @elavegan 🚨🚨Recipe: filled with chickpeas, lentils, peppers, and corn. Then bake in the oven until crispy and also add vegan cheese sauce for serving! So yummy!

Healthy spinach tortillas
1 cup chickpea flour also called garbanzo bean flour (120 g)
1/2 cup tapioca flour/starch (60 g)
2 oz fresh baby spinach leaves (60 g)
1 - 1 1/8 cup water (240-270 ml)
1/3 tsp salt

Instructions
Process all ingredients in your food processor or blender until the batter is smooth. Use 1 cup of water if you plan to make thicker/smaller tortillas for tacos. Add about 1 1/8 cup of water if you want to make thinner/bigger tortillas for e.g. burritos.
Pour about 1/3 cup of the batter into a non-stick skillet. You can add a few drops of oil to the skillet but I made the experience that the tortillas turn out great without oil. Make sure to use a non-stick skillet.
Cook for two minutes on low-medium heat, flip the tortilla and cook on the other side for about one minute. Enjoy your healthy spinach tortillas!
🙏 "Healthy spinach tortillas" elavegan.com

She came home hungry one day, she saw my leftovers in the fridge didn’t even realize they weren’t her leftovers and proceeded to eat half of the pasta that I made. It wasn’t until she went to put the container back in the fridge that she realized she ate the “wrong” pasta haha. So if that doesn’t tell you how good this sauce is I don’t know what is.

VEGAN RICOTTA STUFFED SHELLS!
TAG your friends in comments and grab recipe below! 
ALSO; who wants to see this in a “how to” IG stories? 
These are approved by CHEESE LOVERS... RECIPE 
Ricotta:
1 package organic tofu, firm 
1 cup cashews 
4 tbsp nutritional yeast 
1 tsp salt 
1 tsp garlic powder 
1 tsp onion powder 
pinch of pepper
Juice of 1 lemon 
1/2 cup plain, unsweetened almond milk 
1 (16 ounce) bag frozen spinach

Other ingredients:
25 uncooked jumbo pasta shells
Parsley or cilantro for garnish 
chili pepper flakes for garnish 
Store-bought Marinara sauce OR home made marinara recipe (I put in the comments) 
Method: 
1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
2. Cook the pasta according to the package directions, drain and set aside.
3. Remove tofu from package and wrap in a clean kitchen towel or paper towel and squeeze for 20 seconds to allow for excess water to strain.
4. In a food processor or high speed blender place cashews and pulse until you begin to have a mixture with sand texture. Then add tofu, nutritional yeast, unsweetened almond milk, garlic powder, lemon juice. onion powder, salt & pepper. Blend for 1-2 minutes or until there is no large chunks. Mixture will look slightly  textured… that is okay. Add more almond milk if needed.
5. In a pan over medium to high heat cook frozen spinach for 2-4 minutes just until heated through. 
6. Once ricotta mixture is made and spinach is ready, combine the two in a medium size bowl and mix well. Taste mixture and add any extra salt or seasoning if needed.
7. Grab baking dish and pour 2 cups of marinara sauce on the bottom, spreading sauce evenly. Grab a spoonful of ricotta spinach mixture and spoon it into the cooked pasta shells. Be generous with the filling and then place the stuffed shells
in the baking dish.
8. Once all shells are stuffed place into the oven & bake for 20 minutes. Serve right out of the oven & pour extra marinara sauce on top of each shell. Finish off with a sprinkle of nutritional yeast, chili flakes , fresh herbs and enjoy!

Creamy Tahini Pasta Stir Fry 🙌🏻 We eat pasta at least 1-2 times a week around here and this ones a favorite of ours 😍It’s rich & creamy and goes perfectly with some salmon or tofu🔥You can sub a bean-based pasta for some extra protein, too! Either way, you need this in your life👇🏼👇🏼
8 oz whole wheat pasta, cook as instructed on package
3 cups veggies (I used a kale, cabbage and carrot salad mix)
1 garlic clove
1 tsp sesame oil
Sauce:
3 tbsp tahini
1 tbsp honey
1/3 cup soy sauce 
1/4 cup water
1/2 tsp tapioca flour (can sub regular flour or cornstarch)
Pinch of red pepper flakes

Sauté the veggies on medium heat with the garlic and sesame oil until soft, about 15 minutes. Toss in the pasta and pour in the sauce. Stir together on medium heat until well combined. Top with sesame seeds and red pepper flakes.
Prepping simple and flavorful meals is an easy way to stay healthy throughout the week! 📷: @reversingt2d

Easy Overnight Pizza Dough by @thecuriouschickpea ❤️
.
INGREDIENTS
1 1/2 cups (350g) water, 95 ºF
2 1/2 tsp (14g) salt
1/4 tsp dried instant yeast
4 cups (500g) all purpose flour
.
INSTRUCTIONS
Measure out the warm water in a large mixing bowl. Add in the salt and stir to dissolve. Sprinkle the yeast over the water and let sit for a couple of minutes to hydrate and dissolve, then stir to distribute.
Add the flour into the mixing bowl and stir with a wooden spoon until you form a shaggy dough. Switch to using your hands. Wet your hands to prevent the dough from sticking to them and pinch the dough into several segments between your first finger and thumb. Then reach under the edges of the dough and gently pull it up to stretch the dough until you hit resistance, then fold the section of dough over to rest of the dough. Turn the bowl 1/4 turn and repeat the pulling and folding until you've gone all around. This action brings the dough back into one piece. Repeat the pinching and folding process for about 1-2 minutes until your dough starts to turn into a cohesive, but sticky ball of dough. Re-wet your hands as necessary to prevent the dough from sticking to them. Cover the bowl and let rest for 20 minutes.
After the 20 minutes of rest, turn the dough onto a clean and floured surface. Knead the dough for about 1 minute until you get a smooth ball of dough. Flour your hands and add flour to the counter as necessary to prevent sticking. Lightly coat the mixing bowl with oil and place the ball of dough mixing bowl, turning to coat in oil before leaving seam side down. Cover the mixing bowl and let the dough rise for about 1 hour, until it's doubled in size. You can let it rise for up to 2 hours before shaping.
Turn the dough onto a clean, floured counter and stretch to make a large rectangle. You're going to divide the dough into 2 or 3 pieces (depending on the size you want your final pizza to be) by sprinkling flour over where you're going to cut (this prevents it from sticking) and cut into the sections with a bench scraper, or with a butter knife by pressing straight down into the dough.

Chickpea quinoa burgers (gluten-free, oil-free) by @cookingforpeanuts 🧡
.
In large bowl combine: 1 red onion (small dice), 1 large carrot (grated), large handful baby spinach (roughly chopped), 1-15oz can chickpeas (rinsed + drained), 2 tbsp nutritional yeast, 1 tsp ground cumin, 1 tsp smoked paprika, 1/2 tsp garlic powder, 1/2-3/4 tsp chili powder (or to taste), 3/4 tsp chipotle. Mix well. Add 1-1/2 cups cooked quinoa and mix until evenly incorporated. Add salt to taste. In separate bowl, add 2 cups garbanzo/chickpea flour + 1/4 tsp salt. Gradually add water while mixing until consistency of thick pancake batter. (Should be about 1 cup water.) Add batter to chickpea vegetable quinoa mixture and mix well to combine. Salt to taste. Let sit about 10 minutes. Use hands to form patties of desired size, about 3/4 inch thick. Either pan-fry in a little oil in non-stick skillet or for oil-free bake at 375F on lined sheet until very golden brown (about 25 minutes). For both methods, flip half way. #bestofvegan

Cauliflower & tofu korma by @vegamelon 🧡
.
tofu veggie korma (serves 3-4)
-1/4 cup raw cashews (50g), soaked for 2+ hours
-1 cup full-fat coconut milk (200g)
-1 onion, diced
-4 cloves garlic + 1 tbsp ginger root + 2 green chilis, minced
SPICES: 1 tsp ground coriander, 2 tsp garam masala, 4 whole cloves, 4 cardamom pods, 1/2 tsp each: ground turmeric, ground cumin, chili powder, salt, black pepper
-1/2 cup water
-3 large ripe tomatoes (400g), pureed
-4 cups chopped cauliflower (350g)
-1 package firm tofu, pressed and cubed
-1 cup frozen green peas (120g)
In a blender, blend the soaked cashews and coconut milk into a smooth mixture and set aside. In large pot, heat some oil and add the onion, garlic, ginger, chilis, and spices. Fry the mixture for 5-7 minutes, until fragrant. Mix in tomatoes, cauliflower, and tofu. Cover the pot and let simmer on medium heat for 15 minutes, or until the cauliflower is tender, then stir in peas and coconut mixture. Simmer for 5 more minutes before serving.
#bestofvegan

8-Ingredient Chocolate Peanut Butter Ganache Tart by @panaceas_pantry 💗
.
CRUST.
1 cup almond meal.
1 cup rolled oats.
12 large and soft dates, pitted.
2 Tbsp coconut oil
1 Tbsp maple syrup.
.
Add almond meal and oats to a food processor, and pulse until small crumbs forms. 
2. Add remaining ingredients and pulse till you form a dough. If too dry, add 1-2 more dates. Press dough evenly into a lined tart tin and set aside (mine was 8 inch).
.
GANACHE FILLING.
.
200g vegan dark chocolate (mine was 85%).
1 cup thick coconut milk.
1/4 cup maple syrup.
1/3 cup natural, smooth peanut butter. .
1. Cut chocolate into small chunks and set aside in a large, heat proof bowl. 
2. Add coconut milk and maple syrup to a small saucepan. Heat over medium heat until around 40 degrees Celsius (104F), or just above body temperature. Pour warmed milk over the chocolate, and immediately whisk together until the chocolate melts and you have a creamy ganache. Add peanut butter and whisk through.
3. Pour ganache into tart shell. Set in fridge for a couple of hours, then top with berries (or preferred fruit).
.
To serve: cut gently with a hot knife and serve up with a dollop of coconut yoghurt. #bestofvegan
